releases.name: v2.1.3
releases.body:
AE Timelines v2.1.3 addresses these issues:

- potential security vulnerabilities in `package.devDependencies`
- location of the [test page](http://rhoinc.github.io/ae-timelines/test-page/)

releases.name: v2.1.1
releases.body: AE Timelines v2.1.1 updates the rollup dev dependency and removes the rollup-watch dev dependency to avoid potential security vulnerabilities related to the latter package.  Additionally rollup.config.js has been updated to the latest spec and the interactive example has been moved out of /build to the top-level folder.

releases.name: v2.1.0
releases.body: AE Timelines v2.1.0 adds an [example page](https://rhoinc.github.io/ae-timelines/build/test-page/) and a [settings schema](https://github.com/RhoInc/ae-timelines/blob/master/settings-schema.json).  View a full list of resolved issues [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/ae-timelines/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.1.0+).

releases.name: v2.0.4
releases.body: Fix bug where details table was being drawn on initial load. #39

releases.name: v2.0.3
releases.body: Fix a bug that could cause duplicate controls in certain frameworks #37

releases.name: v2.0.1
releases.body: Filters no longer render with 0 or 1 levels (#28)

releases.name: v2.0.0
releases.body: Version 2.0.0 of the AE Timeline represents a major refactor, and includes many bug fixes and performance improvements. The overall framework using [webcharts-boilerplate](https://github.com/RhoInc/webcharts-wrapper-boilerplate) is still in place, but the secondary build creating a react framework has been removed, and several [configuration options](https://github.com/RhoInc/ae-timelines/wiki/Configuration) have been simplified, breaking backwards compatibility. A full list of resolved issues is available [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/ae-timelines/milestone/2?closed=1).

releases.name: v1.2.1
releases.body: Hotfix to remove option for custom custom filter labels

releases.name: v1.2.0
releases.body:
New features:
- Added `filter_cols` option (and associated `filter_labels` option) for user-specified filters.
- Note added indicating number of participants included in the data / shown in the current view.
- Re-ordered variables in listing shown in details view, and added `detail_cols` option to add additional columns to the table
- Updated gists to use most recent release of hosted libraries.

releases.name: v1.1.0
releases.body:
The framework of the library has been significantly revised (see the [webcharts-wrapper-boilerplate](https://github.com/RhoInc/webcharts-wrapper-boilerplate) library for framework details), but basic functionality remains the same. 

This update also includes full documentation in the [wiki](https://github.com/RhoInc/se-ae-timelines/wiki) and a [standalone example](https://bl.ocks.org/jwildfire/raw/9865b8e7761f28a8a1557622d93ffbde/)
This is the initial release of the AE Timelines, an interactive timeline featuring adverse events plotted by participant over a period of time.

issues.body:
Confirm basic functionality and new features are working as expected in examples shown below:

Examples using v2.0.0 Release Candidate
[default](http://bl.ocks.org/samussiah/raw/0917733a1fda88b274bb482103c84e22/)

**Basic Functionality (Tested every release)**
- [x] Check all spelling and grammar on the page
- [x] View colored plot points and their tooltips for adverse event information by hovering the mouse over the adverse event markers.
- [x] Confirm that the filters (Severity, Subject ID, System Organ Class, Related to Treatment) are working as expected: when selected, only relevant events should be visible along with the ratio and percentage of affected participants
- [x] Confirm that there is an option to sort the visible participants and it works as expected
- [x] Use a combination of sorting and filtering to ensure that more than one manipulation can be applied at once
- [x] Confirm detail view works as expected by clicking on a participant ID

**New Functionality (Tested in V2.0.0 only)**
- [x] (#20) Confirm that the date of an adverse event doesn't end in a circle
- [x] (#19) Confirm that a serious AE is notated by a different mark than a normal AE
- [x] (#26) Confirm that plot points marked as queried appear as a different color than other plot points and when clicked, display a message detailing the event and query

issues.title: Address Backwards compatability in next release
issues.body:
As noted [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/ae-timelines/pull/22#discussion-diff-94696940R11), I think the addition of a new required variable (`ser_col: 'AESER'`) breaks backwards compatibility in the upcoming release. I see 2 options: 

1. Just call this release v2.0.0 instead of v1.3.0 or ..
2. Change the default for `ser_col` to `null` and update the renderer to handle that.

I'm leaning towards option 1 ... @samussiah @brittsikora thoughts? @rtbailey any opinion for ops?

issues.title: User Customizations for details view
issues.body:
Allow users to provide a 2nd settings object to overwrite the default behavior in ./src/bin/second-settings.js.

Might just embed this in the core settings object like: `settings.detailsView = {x = {label = "Custom Label for my Chart"}}`
